        <updateDate>2020-01-30T21:12:12Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b><b>Student Loan Refinancing and Recalculation Act</b></b></p> <p>This bill provides for the refinancing&nbsp;or deferral of certain&nbsp;federal student loans.</p> <p>Specifically, the bill&nbsp;directs the Department of Education to establish a program to refinance the outstanding principal, interest, and late charges on federal student loans in order to give borrowers fixed interest rates equal to the 10-year Treasury note rate plus one percentage point. Further, the bill eliminates origination fees on the loans.</p> <p>In addition, the bill allows borrowers in medical or dental internship or residency programs to defer student loan payments until the completion of their programs.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
